WEBVTT

00:03:29.299 --> 00:03:32.639
where women collect plastic
from all over the city,

00:03:32.663 --> 00:03:34.161
sort it by type,

00:03:34.185 --> 00:03:36.134
shred it, wash it

00:03:36.158 --> 00:03:39.248
and ultimately sell it back
as feedstock to factories

00:03:39.272 --> 00:03:40.640
to make new clothing,

00:03:40.664 --> 00:03:42.431
new plastic buckets

00:03:42.455 --> 00:03:43.616
and chairs.

00:03:44.444 --> 00:03:46.877
Steel is stockpiled separately,

00:03:46.901 --> 00:03:50.831
where the carcasses of cars
and microwaves and washing machines

00:03:50.855 --> 00:03:53.149
become iron rods for new construction;

00:03:53.173 --> 00:03:55.724
where roofing sheets become cookstoves;

00:03:55.748 --> 00:03:59.299
where shafts from cars become chisels

00:03:59.323 --> 00:04:02.830
that are used to scrap more objects;